  • Method Details

    • durationToTicks

      public static long durationToTicks(Duration duration)
      Gets the number of ticks required to cover a duration.

      For example, given a tick duration of 50ms, any duration > 0 ms and <= 50ms will return 1 tick.

      If the duration is negative or zero, 0 is returned.

      Parameters:
      duration - The duration.
      Returns:
      The number of ticks required to cover the duration.

    • getHighestPermissionSuffix

      public static int getHighestPermissionSuffix(org.bukkit.entity.Player player, String permissionBase)
      Retrieves the highest integer value of a specific permission node, if it exists.

      E.g., if a player has two permission nodes: "example.permission.10" and "example.permission.20", then this method would return "20" for a permission base of "example.permission.".

      Parameters:
      player - The player whose permissions to analyze.
      permissionBase - The base permission node to find the suffix for. E.g. "example.permission.".
      Returns:
      The highest integer suffix or -1 if none could be found.
